From 77c3804957ba9b08c413a2698410513b35171211 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Hoffman <alxhoff@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2026 09:44:28 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 25/32] d4xx: Fix state handling and deadlock issues

- Rework locking in ds5_s_ctrl() and ds5_g_volatile_ctrl() to use
  fine-grained per-operation locks instead of holding the mutex across
  the entire function, preventing deadlocks with I2C operations
- Move container_of state resolution before mutex_lock in ds5_s_ctrl()
  to avoid accessing the wrong driver instance under lock
- Use local variables for sensor context (is_rgb, is_depth, etc.)
  so the lock is not held while performing I2C reads/writes
- Drop mutex during stream status polling loop in ds5_mux_s_stream()
  to prevent blocking other driver operations
- Remove problematic stack_trace_print() calls from I2C error paths
  that could cause additional issues under error conditions
